Description: This is a reference to the primary key of the content item associated with this activity.

Column.name: timestamp
Description: This is the date and/or time at which this event occurred.

Column.name: status
Description: This indicates the status of the event. Value values are SUCCESS or FAILURE.  The values come from the TrackingEvent.Status enumeration.

Column.name: event_type
Description: This is the type of activity. For example, PAGE_ACCESS, MODULE_ACCESS, LOGIN_ATTEMPT, etc.  The full list of values is in the TrackingEvent.Type enumueration.

Column.name: internal_handle
Description: This is a reference to the internal_handle of the navigation item associated with the page being accessed.  This is typically populated for PAGE_ACCESS typed events.

Column.name: session_id
Description: This is a reference to the primary key of the user session associated with this activity. Identifies the user session that initiated the action. A session is simply a browser connection to the system launched from an end-user machine.

Column.name: status
Description: This indicates the status of the event. Value values are success (1) or failure (0). The values come from the TrackingEvent.Status enumeration.

Column.name: forum_pk1
Description: This is a reference to the primary key of the discussion forum association with this activity.

Column.name: event_type
Description: This is the type of activity. Groups the event based on what occurred. For example, TAB_ACCESS (page view), PAGE_ACCESS (page view, Triggered when a page, other than a course, organization, content, module, or tab is accessed on the system. The name of the navigation item will be returned.), MODULE_ACCESS, LOGIN_ATTEMPT, LOGOUT, SESSION_TIMEOUT, COURSE_ACCESS (Page view, Triggered when a course frameset is loaded, or when a page is accessed in a course. The name of the navigation item will be returned.), SESSION_INIT (Triggered when a session is initialized), etc. The full list of values is in the TrackingEvent.Type enumueration.

Column.name: data
Description: This contains any free-form text data associated with the event. Data related to the event. This field provides additional information on the event. Each event uses this field, if at all, in different ways. In many instances, the data included in this field is a value that is easily deduced. In some instances, the value in the data field is a number, such as _1_1 or _29_1. These are associated with an EVENT_TYPE of TAB_ACCESS or MODULE_ACCESS. The first number is an ID that references a tab or a module (the second number can be ignored). The ID number that refers to a tab can be found in the user interface by scrolling over the tab. The ID number appears as part of the URL in the status bar.The ID number that refers to a module can be found in the same manner. Scroll over the Maximize, Minimize, or Edit button associated with a module. The ID number will appear as part of the URL in the status bar. Please note that the Detach Module button returns a different ID number and should be ignored.

Column.name: internal_handle
Description: This is a foreign key referencing the internal_handle column of the [AS_CORE].navigation_item table. This is tracked whenever a user accesses a page in the the Academic Suite (eg. When either a PAGE_ACCESS or COURSE_ACCESS event occurs). This will be NULL for events other than PAGE_ACCESS and COURSE_ACCESS. Internal system identifier for the event. This field corresponds to the unique ID in the NAVIGATION_ITEM table. Not all page requests correspond to a navigation item, so this field may often appear blank. If this field is empty, check the CONTENT_PK1 field. If the page accessed displayed content, the primary key for the piece of content will appear in that field.

Column.name: asmt_upgrade_flags
Description: After any import or restore operation the asmt_upgrade_version is set back to 0 and any new data re-upgraded.  There are certain parts of the upgrade which do not have to run in this case (i.e. the upgrade is only required once per course, not after each import operation).  This field is used to store those flags to avoid re-running pieces of the upgrade

Column.name: ultra_status
Value.constraint:
ultra_status_enum
                   N
                          No explicit decision has been made yet (for now treated the same as classic-decided)
          
                   C
                          The classic user experience has explicitly been chosen
          
                   U
                          The Ultra user experience has explicitly been chosen.
          
                   P
                          The course is currently an Ultra course but in preview mode.
Description:
This is the flag indicating if the course is classic, ultra, or ultra preview.  Note that updates to this field are controlled in java code so please do not blindly change it directly.
        Specifically you can only perform these transitions:
        N->C, N->U, N->P, C->U, C->P, P->U, P->C, U->NOTHING. You cannot go back once you pick U
        The NULL value, which represents classic, will be left for all the legacy courses and treated the same as classic

design_template_ck1
                   Y
                          Legacy value. Equivalent to (1)
          
                   N
                          Legacy value. Equivalent to (0)
          
                   0
                          Links only. During a copy operation no files are replicated.

Column.name: pk1
Description: This table really doesn't need a pk1 at all, but our framework dao code likes it when there is a pk1

Description: FK to qti_asi_data if for a question block, for each question in the block; if for a random block, for each referenced source pool in the block.  Deletion of the question (question block case) or pool (random block case) will fail due to this constraint because java code has to be used to remove the reference from the question blocks QTI xml

Column.name: sync_state
Value.constraint:
crs_sync_state_ck
                   I
                          (In Progress) This event is currently being synced.
          
                   E
                          (Error) This single event did not successfully sync during the last try.
          
                   F
                          (Failure) This event and all others in this state experienced a failure which resulted in the entire batch failing to sync.
          
                   S
                          (Stuck) This event has failed after multiple attempts and is stuck.
Description: The current state of this sync event

Column.name: sync_state
Value.constraint:
user_sync_state_ck
                   I
                          (In Progress) This event is currently being synced.
          
                   E
                          (Error) This single event did not successfully sync during the last try.
          
                   F
                          (Failure) This event and all others in this state experienced a failure which resulted in the entire batch failing to sync.
          
                   S
                          (Stuck) This event has failed after multiple attempts and is stuck.
Description: The current state of this sync event

Description: This is a boolean flag (Y/N) indicating if the user name should be highlighted in the stream as moderator or manager. An extra check is done in the java code to check if it still should be highlighted.

Description: FK to course_contents.pk1 if the event is fired in a group discussion (real forum).  This will be NULL if the forum related to this event is not group disscussion. This column is only used for group discussions in an Ultra course.

Description: FK to users.pk1 for the person the action was done against - i.e. a comment on a post would set the post-author in actee_pk1.  This will be NULL if the stream event is not in response to a particular user or if the user was deleted.

Column.name: actor_pk1
Description: FK to users.pk1 for the person doing the action - i.e. a comment on a post would set the commenter in actor_pk1.  This column will be set to NULL if the user was deleted in which case this row should be ignored.

Description: This is a boolean flag (Y/N) indicating if the discussion is within the INDIRECT content area (In Ultra courses an INDIRECT courseToc is created which is not 'visible' to the users in the UI. Column.name: scale_type
Description:
This column defines the type of scale in use. The possible values are below:
        1. T -- Translation, meaning the grade displayed is between a range of possible values, and is calculated using a defined value
        2. S -- Score, the value shown is the points awarded the student out of the total points possible
        3. X -- Text, the value shown is in plain text, where the entry begins with a number, which is calculated as a Score (S)
        4. P -- Percentage, the value shown is the percent out of 100 that the student received
        5. C -- Complete/Incomplete, the value shown has two possible values, complete (C) and incomplete (I)

Column.name: crs_contents_pk1
Description: This is a foreign key referencing the primary key of the course_contents table. This represents the content item from the course or organization that originated this notification. This will be populated when the notification is generated by content, otherwise null.

Column.name: event_type
Description: This is the type of event for this notification item, ie. AVAILABLE or OVERDUE. The specifi A=c type of event, within the course_type, that this represent: Assignment Available, or example, or Assignment Submitted S=Scheduled; A= Available.

Column.name: can_replace_ind
Description: Whether this notification can be replaced by incoming notifications that would normally obviate them. See Notification Replacement for more details. This is a boolean flag (Y/N) indicating whether this notification can be replaced by incoming notifications that would normally obviate them.

Column.name: data_pending_ind
Description: Whether this notification is in the midst of being created - ie, whether it is waiting for its associated recipients to be created. This is a boolean flag (Y/N) indicating whether this notification is in the midst of being created - ie, whether it is waiting for its associated recipients to be created.

Column.name: owner_pk1
Description: This is a foreign key referencing the primary key of the users table. A foreign key reference to the user who created this item, or is responsible for it.

Column.name: parent_id
Description: This is the identifier of the parent item. If this notification is conceptually subordinate to another notifications - as Assignment Submitted is subordinate to Assignment Due, for example - then this column contains the id of the parent notification.

Column.name: dtcreated
Description: This is the date and/or time at which this event occurred. The date on which the item was first added.

Column.name: pk1
Description: This is the surrogate primary key for the table.

Column.name: due_date
Description: This is the due date associated with the source that originated this notification. The date on which this notification is due. Internally, the due date is used to figure out when to send reminders, and also to determine whether transform DUE events into OVERDUE events.

Column.name: source_id
Description: This is the source or content item that originated this notification item. An identifier that uniquely specifies the item on which we're notifying. It's the responsibility of the individual subsystems to ensure that this uniqueness.

Column.name: default_sender_status
Value.constraint:
eud_sender_status
                   U
                          Unprocessed. Waiting for distribution.
          
                   N
                          Notified. Has been disseminated to all distributors.
          
                   F
                          Failed. Distribution failed for all distributors.
          
                   D
                          Deleted. Removed, but retained in the DB for bookkeeping.
          
                   Z
                          Neuter. Never intended to be distributed.
Description: This represents the status of the default sender.

Column.name: crsmain_pk1
Description: This is a foreign key referencing the primary key of the course_main table.

Column.name: important_ind
Description: This is, unfortunately, a very nebulous name for a very specific concept. An important marker indicates that, during a blitz (which is to say, a mass notification) this notification should always be sent out to its recipients, no matter what. See Notification Blitz for more details. This is a boolean flag (Y/N) indicating whether this notification item is important.

Column.name: title
Description: This is the title of the notification item. This will be visible to the user in the UI.

Column.name: parent_content_pk1
Description: This is a foreign key referencing the primary key of the course_contents table. This represents the parent of the content item that originated this notification.

Column.name: start_date
Description: The time when the action happened. The date on which the notification period should begin - which usually maps to the date on which the item will become available. If this is specified, we won't display notification until this date is reached. Note that this is not related to adaptive release rules - those will be evaluated separately and independently.

Column.name: override_setting_ind
Description: Whether this notification should ignore any system/user customizations that would normally suppress its dissemination. This is useful for notifications that absolutely, positively must get out there. This is a boolean flag (Y/N) indicating whether this notification item should be delivered to recipients regardless of their individual notification settings.

Column.name: source_type
Description: This is the source type of the notification item. The class of event this represents: an assignment event, or an assessment event, or a content event, etc

Column.name: end_date
Description: The time when the action ended. The date on which the notification period should end - which usually maps to the date on which the item will become unavailable. If this is specified, we won't display notification after this date is reached. Note that this is not related to adaptive release rules - those will be evaluated separately and independently.

Column.name: default_receiver_status
Value.constraint:
eud_receiver_status
                   U
                          Unprocessed. Waiting for distribution.
          
                   N
                          Notified. Has been disseminated to all distributors.
          
                   F
                          Failed. Distribution failed for all distributors.
          
                   D
                          Deleted. Removed, but retained in the DB for bookkeeping.
          
                   Z
                          Neuter. Never intended to be distributed.
Description: This represents the status of the default receiver.

Description: This is the surrogate primary key for the table.

Column.name: group_pk1
Description: This is a foreign key referencing the primary key of the groups table. If the parent notification is targeted at a group, and this recipient is a member of that group, then this column contains the id of the group.

Column.name: status
Value.constraint:
status
                   U
                          Unprocessed. Waiting for distribution.
          
                   F
                          Notification Digest Pending. Notification has been distributed successfully, and is now awaiting distribution via email digest.
          
                   N
                          Notified. Has been disseminated to all distributors. Digest distributions are still pending.
          
                   D
                          Deleted. Removed, but retained in the DB for bookkeeping.
          
                   Z
                          Neuter. Never intended to be distributed.
Description: This is the status of the notification item for this recipient.

Description: This is a reference to the primary key of the content item associated with this activity.

Column.name: timestamp
Description: This is the date and/or time at which this event occurred.

Column.name: status
Description: This indicates the status of the event. Value values are SUCCESS or FAILURE.  The values come from the TrackingEvent.Status enumeration.

Column.name: event_type
Description: This is the type of activity. For example, PAGE_ACCESS, MODULE_ACCESS, LOGIN_ATTEMPT, etc.  The full list of values is in the TrackingEvent.Type enumueration.

Column.name: internal_handle
Description: This is a reference to the internal_handle of the navigation item associated with the page being accessed.  This is typically populated for PAGE_ACCESS typed events.

Column.name: session_id
Description: This is a reference to the primary key of the user session associated with this activity. Identifies the user session that initiated the action. A session is simply a browser connection to the system launched from an end-user machine.

Column.name: status
Description: This indicates the status of the event. Value values are success (1) or failure (0). The values come from the TrackingEvent.Status enumeration.

Column.name: forum_pk1
Description: This is a reference to the primary key of the discussion forum association with this activity.

Column.name: event_type
Description: This is the type of activity. Groups the event based on what occurred. For example, TAB_ACCESS (page view), PAGE_ACCESS (page view, Triggered when a page, other than a course, organization, content, module, or tab is accessed on the system. The name of the navigation item will be returned.), MODULE_ACCESS, LOGIN_ATTEMPT, LOGOUT, SESSION_TIMEOUT, COURSE_ACCESS (Page view, Triggered when a course frameset is loaded, or when a page is accessed in a course. The name of the navigation item will be returned.), SESSION_INIT (Triggered when a session is initialized), etc. The full list of values is in the TrackingEvent.Type enumueration.

Column.name: data
Description: This contains any free-form text data associated with the event. Data related to the event. This field provides additional information on the event. Each event uses this field, if at all, in different ways. In many instances, the data included in this field is a value that is easily deduced. In some instances, the value in the data field is a number, such as _1_1 or _29_1. These are associated with an EVENT_TYPE of TAB_ACCESS or MODULE_ACCESS. The first number is an ID that references a tab or a module (the second number can be ignored). The ID number that refers to a tab can be found in the user interface by scrolling over the tab. The ID number appears as part of the URL in the status bar.The ID number that refers to a module can be found in the same manner. Scroll over the Maximize, Minimize, or Edit button associated with a module. The ID number will appear as part of the URL in the status bar. Please note that the Detach Module button returns a different ID number and should be ignored.

Column.name: pk1
Description: This is the surrogate primary key for the table.

Column.name: pk1
Description: This is the surrogate primary key for the table.

Column.name: internal_handle
Description: This is a foreign key referencing the internal_handle column of the [AS_CORE].navigation_item table. This is tracked whenever a user accesses a page in the the Academic Suite (eg. When either a PAGE_ACCESS or COURSE_ACCESS event occurs). This will be NULL for events other than PAGE_ACCESS and COURSE_ACCESS. Internal system identifier for the event. This field corresponds to the unique ID in the NAVIGATION_ITEM table. Not all page requests correspond to a navigation item, so this field may often appear blank. If this field is empty, check the CONTENT_PK1 field. If the page accessed displayed content, the primary key for the piece of content will appear in that field.

This field is populated when the EVENT_TYPE is CONTENT_ACCESS.

Column.name: group_pk1
Description: This is a foreign key referencing the primary key of the group table to indicate the Course Group this activity belongs to. This will be NULL if the activity is not Course Group related.

Description: This is a foreign key referencing the primary key of the [AS_CORE].users table to indicate the owner of the activity. This can be NULL if the user cannot be determined. If the user has logged in, then there activity is tied to their user_pk1.

Description: This is a reference to the primary key of the user associated with this activity.

Column.name: course_view_option
Value.constraint:
I
                          Instructors can choose course view at anytime
          
                   U
                          The course will use Ultra view, instructors can't change it
          
                   C
                          The course will use Original view, instructors can't change it
Description:
This is course view option flag. It's different from ultra_status flag, this flag control if instructor can change the course view or change directly by admin,
        while ultra_status just indicate the current course view of this course is.  
        If null, then the default value depends on the system-wide ultra setting:
        If ultra is ON then null is effectively 'I'
        If ultra is OFF then null is effectively 'C'

Column.name: ultra_status
Value.constraint:
ultra_status_enum
                   N
                          No explicit decision has been made yet (for now treated the same as classic-decided)
          
                   C
                          The classic user experience has explicitly been chosen
          
                   U
                          The Ultra user experience has explicitly been chosen.
          
                   P
                          The course is currently an Ultra course but in preview mode.
Description:
This is the flag indicating if the course is classic, ultra, or ultra preview.  Note that updates to this field are controlled in java code so please do not blindly change it directly.
        Specifically you can only perform these transitions:
        N->C, N->U, N->P, C->U, C->P, P->U, P->C, U->NOTHING. You cannot go back once you pick U
        The NULL value, which represents classic, will be left for all the legacy courses and treated the same as classic

Column.name: description

Column.name: position

Column.name: description

Column.name: family

Column.name: navigation_type
Description: Course or System Determines whether the navigation item is available in courses or through the portal. Indicates where the navitem will be used. Possible values: GROUP, COURSE, SYSTEM

Column.name: sub_group
Description: Internal handle sub group.

Column.name: launch_ind
Description: If 'Y', the anchor tags target attribute will have a value of _blank, otherwise it will be _self

Column.name: internal_handle
Description: Internal handle.

Column.name: enabled_mask
Description: This the bit mask that determines if the tool is enabled or not. SYSTEM = 0x00000001, COURSE = 0x00000002, ORG = 0x00000004, COURSE_GROUP = 0x00000008, ORG_GROUP = 0x00000010, NAVITEM_COURSE = 0x00000001, NAVITEM_ORG = 0x00000002, NONE = 0x00000000, ALL = 0xffffffff.

Column.name: pk1
Description: This is the surrogate primary key for the table.

Column.name: entitlement_uid
Description: Defines the entitlement required to access the item. Entitlement required to use this navitem. There are many entitlements in the entitlement table to chose from, e.g., system.admin.VIEW, Modify, etc

Column.name: application
Description: Application accessed through the navigation item. Application module, e.g: instructor_gradebook, course_email, discussion_board, etc.

Column.name: redirect_url
Description: Some navigation items, such as the Lost Password page, may be redirected. If allowed, the redirected URL appears in this field. This is navigation redirect url. If set it will override the href (Some license levels let the administrator configure this)

Column.name: src
Description: Image or icon connected to the navigation item.

Column.name: label
Description: Internal handle label.

Column.name: user_label
Description: This is customized label. If set it will override the label.

Column.name: launch_ind
Description: Determines whether or not to launch the application in a separate browser window. if 'Y', the anchor tags target attribute will have a value of _blank, otherwise it will be _self

Column.name: visible_ind
Description: Determines whether or not the item is visible to users. if 'N', this is equivalent to disabling the nav item, but not in all situations.

Column.name: internal_handle
Description: Internal handle.

Column.name: application
Description: Application module, e.g: instructor_gradebook, course_email, discussion_board, etc.

Column.name: actee_pk1
Description: FK to users.pk1 for the person the action was done against - i.e. a comment on a wiki page would set the post-author in actee_pk1.  This will be NULL if the stream event is not in response to a particular user or if the user was deleted.

Column.name: pk1
Description: This is the surrogate primary key for the table.

Column.name: actor_pk1
Description: FK to users.pk1 for the person doing the action - i.e. a comment on a wiki page would set the commenter in actor_pk1.  This column will be set to NULL if the user was deleted in which case this row should be ignored.

Column.name: wiki_entry_title
Description: Wiki entry title at the time of the event - This will be NULL if the event has nothing to do with wiki comments or if it is a deletion event. This corresponds to XYF_PROPERTIES.SHORT_STRING_VALUE

Column.name: crsmain_pk1
Description: FK to course_main for the course in which the event occurs.  Will be set to NULL if the course was deleted.

Column.name: group_pk1
Description: FK to groups for the group in which the event occurs.  This will be NULL for non group wikis or if the group was deleted.

Column.name: event_date
Description: Date and time the event occurred.

Column.name: course_contents_pk1
Description: FK to course_contents.pk1 if the event pertains to a course contents item.  This will be NULL if the event does not have a course_contents.pk1 or if the course content was deleted.

Column.name: event_type
Value.constraint:
wiki_stream_event_type_ck
                   EP
                          Wiki entry posted event
          
                   EE
                          Wiki entry edited event
          
                   ED
                          Wiki entry deleted event
          
                   CP
                          Wiki comment posted event
          
                   CD
                          Wiki comment deleted event

Column.name: event_text
Description: Text specific to this event - not the stream text directly, but the dynamic text to substitute into an event-appropriate message when rendering the stream. This will be NULL for deletion events.

Column.name: event_title
Description: Title for the stream event - This will be NULL for deletion events.

Column.name: wiki_pk1
Description: This is a foreign key referencing the primary key of the wiki table.

Column.name: wiki_entry_id
Description: Wiki entry pageGuid - This will be NULL if the event has nothing to do with wiki entry. This is made up of 32 character hex digits created from UuidFactory.

Column.name: wiki_entry_version
Description: Wiki entry version - This will be NULL if the event has nothing to do with wiki entry.

Column.name: wiki_comment_id
Description: Wiki comment id - This will be NULL if the event has nothing to do with wiki comments. This corresponds to XYF_COMMENTS.COMMENT_ID

Column.name: wiki_title
Description: Wiki title at the time of the event - This corresponds to WIKI.NAME
